place.name: WOOD WALTON
place.gazetteerText: WOODWALTON, a parish in the district and county of Huntingdon; on the Great Northern railway, 4¾ miles S by E of Holme r. station, and 6 N by W of Huntingdon. Post town, Sawtry, under Peterborough. Acres, 3,718. Real property, £3,485. Pop., 388. Houses, 77. The manor belongs to R. H. Hussey, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Ely. Value, £534.* Patron, R. H. Hussey, Esq. The church was repaired in 1859. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
